RoyaltyInfo
├── when no default or token royalty is set
│   └── it should return zero address and zero royalty amount
├── when only default royalty is set
│   └── it should return the default receiver and salePrice * defaultFee / FEE_DENOMINATOR
├── when only token-specific royalty is set
│   └── it should return the token-specific receiver and salePrice * tokenFee / FEE_DENOMINATOR
├── when both default and token-specific royalty are set
│   └── it should prefer the token-specific royalty over the default
├── when sale price is zero
│   └── it should return zero royalty amount while preserving the configured receiver
└── when royalty fee is zero
    └── it should return zero royalty amount while preserving the configured receiver

DefaultRoyalty
├── SetDefaultRoyalty
│   ├── when called with a valid receiver and fee <= FEE_DENOMINATOR
│   │   └── it should set the default royalty receiver and fraction
│   ├── when called multiple times with different values
│   │   └── it should overwrite the previous default royalty receiver and fraction
│   ├── when called with fee equal to zero
│   │   └── it should set default royalty with zero fraction but keep the receiver
│   ├── when called with fee greater than FEE_DENOMINATOR
│   │   └── it should revert with ERC2981InvalidDefaultRoyalty
│   └── when called with the zero address as receiver
│       └── it should revert with ERC2981InvalidDefaultRoyaltyReceiver
└── DeleteDefaultRoyalty
    ├── when a default royalty is set and then deleted
    │   └── it should clear the default royalty receiver and fraction in storage
    ├── when a default royalty is deleted and no token-specific royalty exists
    │   └── royaltyInfo should return zero address and zero royalty amount
    └── when a default royalty is deleted but token-specific royalty exists
        └── royaltyInfo for tokens with token-specific royalty should remain unchanged

TokenRoyalty
├── SetTokenRoyalty
│   ├── when called with a valid receiver and fee <= FEE_DENOMINATOR
│   │   └── it should set the token-specific royalty receiver and fraction for that tokenId
│   ├── when called for multiple tokenIds
│   │   └── it should maintain independent royalty settings per tokenId
│   ├── when called again for the same tokenId
│   │   └── it should overwrite the previous token-specific royalty receiver and fraction
│   ├── when called with fee equal to zero
│   │   └── it should set token-specific royalty with zero fraction but keep the receiver
│   ├── when called with fee greater than FEE_DENOMINATOR
│   │   └── it should revert with ERC2981InvalidTokenRoyalty
│   └── when called with the zero address as receiver
│       └── it should revert with ERC2981InvalidTokenRoyaltyReceiver
└── ResetTokenRoyalty
    ├── when token-specific royalty exists and default royalty is set
    │   └── it should clear token-specific royalty and cause royaltyInfo to fall back to the default royalty
    ├── when token-specific royalty exists and no default royalty is set
    │   └── it should clear token-specific royalty and cause royaltyInfo to return zero address and zero royalty amount
    └── when multiple tokenIds have token-specific royalty and some are reset
        └── it should only clear royalty for the reset tokenIds and leave the others unchanged

Sequences
├── when default royalty is set, then token-specific royalty is set, then token-specific royalty is reset
│   └── royaltyInfo should first use the default, then the token-specific, then fall back to the default again
└── when default royalty is set, multiple tokens have different token-specific royalties, and default royalty is deleted
    ├── royaltyInfo for tokens with token-specific royalty should continue using their token-specific configuration
    └── royaltyInfo for tokens without token-specific royalty should return zero address and zero royalty amount

EdgeCases
├── when sale price and fee create fractional royalty amounts
│   └── it should compute the royalty amount correctly without overflow
├── when sale price is very large but below overflow thresholds
│   └── it should compute the royalty amount without reverting
├── when tokenId is zero
│   └── it should behave the same as for other valid tokenIds
└── when tokenId is the maximum uint256 value
    └── it should behave the same as for other valid tokenIds

